MOH Announcement: 27TH JAN 2020

The seventh patient confirmed to be infected with the virus was a 35-year-old man from Wuhan, who arrived in Singapore on Jan 23. 

He developed symptoms on Jan 24 and went to Raffles Hospital. He was then transferred to NCID by private ambulance, MOH said.

The man tested positive for the coronavirus on Jan 27 at 11pm. 

Prior to his admission, he stayed at Marina Bay Sands, MOH added. 

On Feb 4, he became the first coronavirus patient in Singapore to be discharged after he "comprehensively tested negative" for the virus, said the ministry.